      /* TESSDescriptiveStatsandBaselineDemand.do */
/** 
TESS Descriptive Statistics and Baseline demand 
@author Allcott and Taubinsky */

/* DESCRIPTIVE STATS */
use Calculations/PreppedTESSData.dta, clear
/* Randomization Checks */
global SumStatVars = "WTP1 $DemographicVars"
foreach var in $SumStatVars {
	sum `var' [aweight=Weight] 
	reg `var' T [pweight=Weight], robust
	reg `var' TP [pweight=Weight], robust, if TP==1|T==0
}


foreach var in $SumStatVars {
	sum `var' [aweight=Weight]
		local `var'_mean_T = r(mean)
		local `var'_sd_T = r(sd)
	
	reg `var' T [pweight=Weight], robust
		local `var'_TCb = _b[T]
		local `var'_TCse = _se[T]
	
	*reg `var' TP [pweight=Weight], robust, if TP==1|T==0
	reg `var' TP [pweight=Weight], robust, if T==1
		local `var'_TPCb = _b[TP]
		local `var'_TPCse = _se[TP]
}

* For F-tests
reg T $SumStatVars [pweight=Weight], robust
reg TP $SumStatVars [pweight=Weight], robust, if T==1


clear
gen Variable = ""
gen T = .
*gen TP = .
*gen C = .
gen TC = .
gen TPC = .

foreach var in $SumStatVars {
	sum T
	local N_2 = r(N)+2
	set obs `N_2'
	replace Variable = "`var'" if _n==_N-1
	foreach group in T {
		replace `group' = ``var'_mean_`group'' if _n==_N-1
		replace `group' = ``var'_sd_`group'' if _n==_N
	}
	foreach comp in TC TPC {
		replace `comp' = ``var'_`comp'b' if _n==_N-1
		replace `comp' = ``var'_`comp'se' if _n==_N
	}
}
outsheet using Output/TESSLightbulbsSumStats.csv, comma names replace


/* Heterogeneous Baseline Demand */
outreg,clear
use Calculations/PreppedTESSData.dta, clear


reg WTP1 $DemographicVars beta delta [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep($DemographicVars beta delta)

* "The results in column 1 rule out with 90 percent confidence that a one standard deviation increase in � increases WTP for the CFL by more than $0.47."
local betabound = _b[beta]+1.65*_se[beta]
sum beta [aw=Weight]
display r(sd)*`betabound'


* Individual variables correlated with greenness
reg WTP1 Liberal [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(Liberal)

reg WTP1 Party [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(Party)

		
reg WTP1 Environmentalist [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(Environmentalist)
		
				
reg WTP1 ConserveEnergy [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(ConserveEnergy)
		
**** Agency Problem explanation
reg WTP1 OwnHome [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(OwnHome)

**** Present Bias explanation
reg WTP1 beta delta [pweight=Weight], robust 
	outreg, se merge replace varlabels tex fragment starlevels(10 5 1) statfont($statfontsize) summstat(r2 \ N) ///
		keep(beta delta)

		
outreg using "Output/TESSHeterogeneousBaselineDemand", replay replace tex fragment statfont($statfontsize) ///
				ctitles("","(1)","(2)","(3)","(4)","(5)","(6)","(7)") 

	
/* Robustness */
* Check unweighted. Estimates very similar.
reg WTP1 $DemographicVars beta delta, robust
